        "action": "Repeal Restriction of Offensive Weapons Act 1959 amended 1961",
        "additional_details": "Please don't take my word for it, read the sources yourself and please consider another perspective apart from your own. We all benefit from talking\r\n\r\nRestriction of Offensive Weapons Act 1959:\r\nhttp://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/Eliz2/7-8/37\r\n\r\nRestriction of Offensive Weapons Act 1961 Amendment:\r\nhttp://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/Eliz2/9-10/22\r\n\r\n\"The Toy That Kills\" article that started mass hysteria of \"flick knives\" which are knives that open by the push of a button:\r\nhttp://bayimg.com/oajmkAagC",
        "background": "The Restriction of Offensive Weapons Act 1959 (amended in 1961) banned the importation, manufacture, sale, hiring, lending\r\nof knives that are not manually opened by hand, and not locked\r\nin place by hand.\r\n\r\nShould the mechanism of a knife should determine it's legality? I don't believe it should.",
